  <other_name type="common_name">Crocea iceplant</other_name>
  <discussion>Malephora crocea is grown as an ornamental and often sold as a ground cover for
    landscaping. It is cultivated along freeways as far north and inland as Fresno,
    California.</discussion>
  <discussion>Two varieties of Malephora crocea have been recognized: var. crocea, with the adaxial
    surfaces of the petals orange and the abaxial surfaces purplish; and var. purpureocrocea
    (Haworth) H. Jacobsen &amp; Schwantes, with petals purplish on both surfaces, which is grown for
    ornamental purposes and is not naturalized in the flora.</discussion>
